  "text": "In summary, Johnson et al [CITATION_1] have characterized a platelet-mediated pathway by which Tamoxifen and its metabolite 4-OH indirectly restrain angiogenesis and metastasis. Although these compounds directly affect breast cancer cells by causing estrogen deprivation, platelets exposed to Tamoxifen can potentially limit tumor progression in situ ",
